# kaiiak — General Project Rules

## Language

- Always respond to the user in **French**
- All code, comments, docstrings, variable/function/class names must be in **English**
- Django `verbose_name`, `help_text`, admin labels: **English**

## Commits

Never commit without explicit user permission.

```
✅ Triggers: "commit", "fais un commit", "pousse ça"
❌ NOT triggers: "prends des actifs", "sauvegarde", "backup", "c'est bon"
```

## Git Branch Strategy

```
dev       ← daily work
staging   ← push from dev
main      ← PR from staging only, never force push
```

Deploy to staging:
```bash
git fetch origin && git checkout staging && git merge origin/dev --no-edit && git push origin staging && git checkout dev
```

Never `git push --force` on `main`.

## Paths (inside Docker container)

- All Django code: `/app/code/project/`
- Documentation: `/app/docs/`
- Never write code under `/app/project/` or `/app/`
